standard multi-purpose move in this position - Black prevents Ng5 and Bg5 
intrusions while making the ...Nf6-h7-g5 manoeuvre possible.} 8. c3 {[%cal 
Bd3d4] It is logical to try exploit Black's slow play with a central pawn break 
(d3-d4).} Nh7 {[%cal Bh7g5,Bf7f5] If Black doesn't play this now, I don't see 
the point of ...h6. The idea is of course ...Ng5, which is played to trade off a 
pair of knights but more importantly also trade off Black's dark bishop (which 
is his 'bad' bishop due to the pawns being on its colour). In addition, ...Nh7 
also prepares a future ...f5 pawn break.} 9. a5 {[%cal Ba5a6][%csl Ga5,Rb7] 
White gains more space on the queenside and prevents any possible ...Na5 or 
...a5 idea.} a6 {Black decides to stop the pawn in its tracks - 10. a6 could be 
quite annoying otherwise.} 10. Nbd2 {[%cal Bd2f1,Bf1e3,Bf1g3] Natural 
